Can we start by building a command line interface to talk to Phantomaton in this repository? You can tell me which files to create and commands to run, and I'll follow your lead generally and provide guidance where I can. I'd like to do this as a NodeJS application, although we'll probably want to branch out to Python later.

Here's a code sample of a call to the Anthropic API:

```
const getResponse = async (messages) => {
  const system = readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, 'system.md'), 'utf-8');
  const payload = { model: 'claude-3-haiku-20240307', max_tokens: 4096, messages, system };
  const headers = {
    Accept: 'application/json',
    'x-api-key': process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
    'anthropic-version': '2023-06-01',
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  };
  const fetched = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', {
    body: JSON.stringify(payload),
    headers,
    method: 'POST',
  });
  const { role, content } = await fetched.json();
  return { role, content };
};
```

For good or ill, I'm using `node-fetch` to provide `fetch` APIs in that example.

